text: Hector John Sutherland was a racing cyclist from Australia. He was born on 6 March 1930 and died on 26 April 2011. He took second place in the Australian National Road Race Championships in 1953 and 1954 and took first place at the 1950 Commonwealth Games. == References == == Other websites == Category:1930 births Category:2011 deaths Category:Australian cyclists Category:Sportspeople from Victoria (Australia)
